HEADWORD: fractionation
<hw>frac`tion*a"tion</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the act or process of
separating a mixture into portions of different composition, as in
distillation or <cref>fractional crystallization</cref>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fractional process.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Petroleum industry)</fld> <def>Separation of crude
oil into components of differing composition by <cref>fractional
distillation</cref>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fractious</ent>⟦br⟧
